							<h1>Safety Inspection</h1>
							<!--<div id="module-left">
								<iframe width="240" height="200" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/kJqZ58RmBJM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
							</div>-->
							<p>The safety inspection is a test conducted for labors working at heights to make sure that proper safety standards are in place for workers who work at elevations. There are safety standards set by the law that applies to all workplaces in the construction sector. A safety inspection is to check whether the contractors are working within the defined safety standards or if there is any negligence in ensuring the safety and protection of the workers.<br></p><p>There are many programs designed to meet the safety standards and safety inspections are necessary as it checks all the details that cannot be overlooked when labor are working at heights. The prime aim is to make the labor secure and check for any reasons that can lead to an accident or a serious injury to a person working on elevation. <a href='http://sayfasystems.co.uk/solutions/sims/' title='harness and lanyard inspection'>harness and lanyard inspection</a> and other apparatus testing are required to check the measures of <a href='http://sayfasystems.co.uk' title='fall protection'>fall protection</a> for the labor and check the quality of the safety equipment used during the labor operations.<br></p><p><span><a href='http://sayfasystems.co.uk/solutions/sims/' title='harness and lanyard inspection'>Read more about harness and lanyard inspection</a></span><br></p><p><strong>A safety inspection for working at heights includes the following:</strong></p><p>- The complete inspection of all equipment used at heights.<br>- The rules for setting up security mechanisms for workers on <br>- Checking all protective gears such as guardrails, belts, and steel railings.<br>- Provide on-site training to contractors and labors on all protective measures for safety and security of workers.</p><p>The safety tests is an operation that licensed officials conduct and they inspect machinery and pieces of equipment that are the main tools for constructions at heights. There are many safety measures on a defined set of parameters. The workers go through a checking routine to see if they have the proper gear to work on certain heights such as protective jackets and eye glasses .  The inspection teams look for faults in all the equipment such as belts, railings, steel supports, and the surface area where workers work on height.</p><p>Many contractors conduct there own safety checks to ascertain that all safety standards implemented by them are functional and there is no negligence over the safety of the workers. The safety of the worker is not only the moral responsibility of the contractor but it is a legal requirement. Failure to comply with the safety standards can lead to regulatory action against the contractors, and a business can be penalized or shut down completely over poor safety standards.</p><p>There is much emphasis on the safety parameters to work on height as the risk of working on height is far greater and any negligence can result in serious injuries or death of a worker. Many new safety standards are introduced and the contractors and businesses are expected to keep their safety measures up to the current requirements.  The safety parameters are set by consulting experts from all sectors such as builders, labor organization, safety firms and other industries.</p><p>To improve and enhance the safety of workers who work at elevations the implementation of all safety standards and proper maintenance of safety equipment should be the top priority.</p>							<!--<div id="module-right">
